<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-17T14:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-17T14:29:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/302</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-17T14:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram March 16, 6 p.m. Owner here yesterday talked with me,
                            President and commander of military forces of his district. The
                            Government promised to send more troops this morning. I received
                            telephone from the Consular agent at Caibarien saying that young Atkins
                            at Punta Alegre alarmed fearing attack from Spanish bandit; they wish
                            marines. He reported all mills except his grinding. I gave information
                            to the Navy and informed the President. He telegraphed immediately
                            commander of military district. Owner of the place says this menace is
                            from an old Spanish bandit with ninety followers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>